caption:
I’m coming home!! Thank you for following along this incredible journey with me. Thank you to my family, friends, & colleagues for your constant love & support! My son wrote/produced a special song about my journey called “Touch The Stars”, now I know was all worth it. Read my final entry into the Captain’s Log.
https://nasa.tumblr.com/post/174477201464/astronaut-journal-entry-to-touch-the-stars
‪My last night...goodnight @iss! LAB at night, taken by @astro_feustel.
‪Congratulations Lead Flight Director Gary Horlacher at @nasajohnson, Lead POD Pat Patterson at @nasa_marshall and the entire Expedition 55 team! Well Done!! Viper Flight Rocks!!‬
Recovery is going great - it is nice to be home!

CONGRATULATIONS Blue Hills Regional High School Class of
2018! Well done!

#FlashbackFriday to my 3rd week on @iss! It’s crazy to think that in 3 weeks I’ll be back home, time flies! Read my 4th journal entry about science, sunrises, and our space themed movie night! 
https://nasa.tumblr.com/post/173925952939/astronaut-journal-entry-week-3

168 days in space. What a journey! So many incredible science experiments & memories made with my crewmates. Find out the 5 things I’ll miss most about living on @iss in my journal entry! 
https://nasa.tumblr.com/post/174436148699/astronaut-journal-entry-the-last-week

‪The coolest suit I’ve ever worn to work! Read my journal entry about my first #Spacewalk! 
https://nasa.tumblr.com/post/173960818719/astronaut-journal-entry-spacewalking ‬

It’s difficult to describe the feeling of excitement as I prepared to blast off to the @iss for my first flight, but I did my best to share my experience with you all! Read my first journal entry from the night before my launch here: https://nasa.tumblr.com/post/173765152339/astronaut-journal-entry-pre-launch
